`_paginate_body` in `operations.py` (line ~1159) calls `body.splitlines()` unconditionally and slices the resulting line array. Entry blocks are multi-line HTML structures (`<div><sub>timestamp</sub>\n\ncontent\n</div>`) â€” a line-based slice cuts through them arbitrarily.

